node.text:
When it comes to brain health & functionality @davidperlmutter knows what he’s talking about! 
Dr. Perlmutter is a board certified neurologist & @nytimes best selling author of publications “Brain Wash” , “Grain Brain” & “The Surprising Truth about Wheat, Carbs, & Sugar” to name a few.

In this episode he educates us on ways to alleviate & manage stress levels ,as well as look after our overall mental health.

For more info on Dr. Perlmutter visit:

https://www.drperlmutter.com

#selfcare #selfcareathome #mentalhealth

node.title: The Self Care Series: MENTAL HEALTH & MANAGING STRESS

node.text:
A conversation with Hypnotherapist, Coach & Author of "The Anxiety Solution" Chloe Brotheridge, on ways to manage and successfully treat anxiety.

Anxiety is the most common of all mental disorders, currently affecting around one in thirteen people worldwide. Anxiety disorders are highly treatable , yet less than 40% of those suffering will receive adequate treatment. I hope this helps you or someone you know.

Hey Insta Fam! 👋🏽🥰
Just checking in to say I hope you’ve all been kind to yourselves lately & are having a Splendid start to September!

Ya girl is finallyyy out of quarantine & excited to be back on home ground for a few days. 🤸🏽‍♀️🇬🇧

I’ve already hit up @nandosuk three times, loitered in the @marksandspencer food hall on the daily & eaten my body weight in @cadburyuk chocolate. 😋 The simple things. 

If you’re new here Thanks for joining the party. I see you!
👀❤️
